:INFO
The Heist Novel That Made Me Laugh Out Loud on a Train
The Lies of Locke Lamora is about a gang of thieves called the Gentleman Bastards \
who operate in Camorr, a fantasy city built on the ruins of an alien civilization. \
Scott Lynch writes with a propulsive energy and a very dry wit that produces the \
most entertaining heist plot I have found in any genre. The scene where Locke \
attempts to bluff his way past a crime lord using nothing but his confidence is \
the funniest thing I have read in fantasy and possibly the best thing in the book.

